                    <msContents>
                        <summary/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer for gaining respect</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ሀሊም፡ ሀሊም፡ ሀሊም፡ ሀሊም፡ ሀሊም፡ ሀሊም፡ ሀሊም፡ ወከመ፡ ቢስርቀያድ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ፲ወ፬አስማተ፡ ርብሽመ፡ ከማሁ፡ ሙሮሸብአ፡
                                ለሰብአ፡ ጋላ፡ ወለሻንቅላ፡ ወለሰብአ፡ ኵሉ፡ ፍጥረት፡ በግርማ፡ ገጸ፡ ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <note>Written in the left column under the third picture.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2393tabiba">Ṭabiba ṭabibān</title>
                            <note>First stanza of the hymn. Written in the left column under the third picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> እግዚአብሔር፡ ጠቢበ፡ ጠቢባን፡ ከሃሊ፤ እስመ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ እምጥንት፡ አንተ፡
                                ኢትበሊ፤ ድኩመ፡ ሕሊና፡ ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7115LanceWounds">Ṣalot baʾǝnta kʷināt ...</title>
                            <note>Written in the middle and right columns under the third picture and in the left column under the fourth picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ኵናት፡ በስመ፡ ሀለኩ፡ ኸቢር፡ ኑራሂ፡ ሰላም፡ ኢኢዙቢላሂ፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer against lance wounds</title>
                            <note>Written in the middle and right columns under the fourth picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ኵናት፡ ወደራግ፡ ወደራግ፡ ወደራግ፡ ወደራግ፡ ወደራግ፡ ወደራግ፡ በጀን፡ በጀን፡ በአለማ፡ በቅድመ፡ ገጸ፡ 
                                ገ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">ጸ</supplied>በርከ፡ አርዕዶሙ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                            <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2866RepCh147#10">Salām to George of Lydda</title>
                            <note>Stanza 10 of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2866RepCh147">Malkǝʾa Giyorgis</ref>, written in the left and middle columns under the 
                                fifth picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለከናፍሪከ፡ እለ፡ ተከሥታ፡ ለዘምሮ። ስመ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ መምለክያነ፡ ጣዖት፡ ለአስተሐፍሮ። ጊዮርጊስ፡ ልዳዊ፡ ዕጉሥ፡ 
                                ለተጽእሮ። ፈረስከ፡ ዘትፄዓኖ፡ እንደ፡ ያስተቃንጽ፡ ዕግሮ። ለረዊደ፡ ጸርየ፡ ይሩጽ፡ ወኢያንትግ፡ በጽሮ።</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i6">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7120Respect">Kamāhu ʾaššabromu la-sabʾa kʷǝllu fǝṭrat...</title>
                            <note>Written in the right column under the fifth picture and in the left and middle column under the sixth picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ዑን፡ ዑን፡ ዑን፡ ዑን፡ ዑን፡ ዑን፡ ዑን፡ ነቢ፡ ነቢ፡ ነቢ፡ ነቢ፡ ነቢ፡ ነቢ፡ ነቢ፡ ሰላማ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ከማሁ፡ አሸብሮሙ፡ ለሰብአ፡ ኵሉ፡ ፍጥረት፡
                                በግርማ፡ ገጸ፡ ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i7">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer for gaining respect from Gāllā, Šānqǝllā and all kinds of people</title>
                            <note>Written in the right column under the sixth picture and in the three columns under the seventh picture. The text is 
                                partly similar to the prayer above, but using several 
                                <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic">magic words (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾasmāt</foreign>)</term> at the beginning. 
                                The letter <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዥ</foreign> is represented by the more ancient or irregular form with four little 
                                strokes marking the sixth order: <figure><graphic url="https://betamasaheft.eu/resources/images/snippets/BLorient12996/sign2.png" height="30px">
                                <desc>Symbol as represented in the catalogue by Stefan Strelcyn</desc></graphic></figure>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ዥኖ፡ ከሚጽ፡ ከሚጽ፡ ከሚጽ፡ ከሚጽ፡ ከደቢል፡ እልሚል፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ከማሁ፡ አሸብሮሙ፡ ለሰብአ፡ ጋላ፡ ወለሰብአ፡ ሻንቅላ፡ ወለሰብአ፡
                                ኵሉ፡ ፍጥረት፡ በግርማ፡ ገጸ፡ ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i8">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer for gaining respect from Gāllā, Šānqǝllā and all kinds of people</title>
                            <note>Written in the left and middle columns under the eighth picture. The text is partly similar to the two prayers above, 
                                but using different <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic">magic words (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾasmāt</foreign>)</term> at the 
                                beginning.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ ሽሐብር፡ ስለከላሂምሸርታ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ 
                                አሸ<surplus>ብ</surplus>ብሮሙ፡ ለሰብአ፡ ጋላ፡ ወለሻንቅላ፡ ወለሰብአ፡ ኵሉ፡ ፍጥረት፡ 
                                በግርማ፡ ገጸ፡ ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i9">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7116RingSolomon">Za-nabara wǝsta ḫǝlqatu la-Salomon...</title>
                            <note>Written in the right column under the eighth picture, in the three columns under the ninth picture and in the left 
                                column under the tenth picture. The text is partly similar to the two prayers above, but using different 
                                <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic">magic words (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾasmāt</foreign>)</term> at the 
                                beginning which are said to originate from the ring of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8925Solomon">Solomon</persName>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ ቀወአረቢ፡ ሂሙፋርክሩክናኤል፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> አቅማሐሹን፡ ዘነበረ፡ ውስተ፡ ኅልቀቱ፡ ለሰሎሞን፡ ንጉሥ፡
                                ከማሁ፡ አሸብሮሙ፡ ለሰብአ፡ ጋላ፡ ወለሻንቅላ፡ ወለሰብአ፡ ዛቲ፡ ዓለም፡ በግርማ፡ ገጸ፡ ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i10">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer for gaining respect from pagans</title>
                            <note>Written in the right column under the eighth picture, in the three columns under the ninth picture and in the left 
                                column under the tenth picture. The text is partly similar to the two prayers above, but using different 
                                <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic">magic words (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾasmāt</foreign>)</term> at the 
                                beginning.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ርብዓም፡ ደርዓም፡ በደርዓም፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ አሸብሮሙ፡ ለአረሚ፡ በግርማ፡ ገጸ፡ 
                                ገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i11">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer against enemies</title>
                            <note>Written in the two middle columns under the tenth picture. The text is another prayer using secret names as those
                                directly above seeking protection against <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH1508Gallai">Gāllā</persName>, 
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH2043sanqel">Šānqǝllā</persName> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾarami</foreign> (pagans).</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ኃይለ፡ ፀላዒ፡ ወፀር፡ ቀጅ፡ መቀጅ፡ እልጓሕስም፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/>
                                በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ ንፍድ፡ ሙቦል፡ ወምጽልአ፡ አዕይንቲሆሙ፡ ለሰብአ፡ አረሚ፡ ወ<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH2043sanqel">ሻንቅላ፡</persName>
                                ከመ፡ ኢይንሥኡ፡ ፀብአ፡ ላዕሌየ፡ ለቀቲለ፡ ሰብእናየ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/> ወይኵኑ፡ ከመ፡ ዕብን፡ ፍዙዛነ፡ 
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH1508Gallai">ጋላ፡</persName> ወ<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH2043sanqel">ሻንቅላ፡</persName> ወአረሚ፡ 
                                <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ድፍን፡ ልቦሙ፡ ወአጽልም፡ አእይንቲሆሙ፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i12">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6477PPAynaTela">Prayer against enemies and for being loved</title>
                            <note>Written in the right column under the tenth picture and in the left column under the eleventh picture. 
                                The beginning of the prayer is taken from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Psalm 3</ref>. 
                                The letter <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዥ</foreign> is represented by the more ancient or irregular form with four little 
                                strokes marking the sixth order: 
                                <figure><graphic url="https://betamasaheft.eu/resources/images/snippets/BLorient12996/sign2.png" height="30px">
                                <desc>Symbol as represented in the catalogue by Stefan Strelcyn</desc></graphic></figure>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">እግዚኦ፡ ሚበዝኁ፡ እለ፡ ይሣቅዩኒ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በዥርሮ፡ በዥርሮ፡ ድንፍ፡ ልቦሙ፡ ወአጽልም፡ አዕይንቲሆሙ፡ ወአጽርዕ፡
                                እንግልጋሆሙ፡ ወአብህም፡ አፉሆሙ፡ ወአልስህ፡ ኅምዞሙ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይትናገሩኒ፡ ነገረ፡ ኅሱም፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ፍቅር፡ ወሰላም፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i13">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer against enemies</title>
                            <note>Prayer against various enemies fighting the owner of the scroll with all kinds of weapons. Text is written in the first 
                                or second column under the eleventh picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ለአናንያ፡ ወአዛርያ፡ ወሚሳኤል፡ ስምከ፡ እጼውዕ፡ እንዘ፡ እብል፡ በከመ፡ ጸውዓት፡ እምከ፡ እንዘ፡ ትብል፡ ስምከ፡ ልራፑን፡ ሐራፑን፡ 
                                ሹሐል፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ አርኅቆመ፡ እምኔየ፡ ለእለ፡ ይደ<surplus>፡</surplus> ብዩኒ፡ አእላፍ፡ በየማንየ፡ ወአእላፍ፡ በጸጋምየ፡ 
                                <gap reason="ellipsis"/> እለ፡ ኀቤየ፡ በመዓልት፡ ወበሌሊት፡ ለቀቲለ፡ ሰብእናየ፡ ጸዊሮሙ፡ ወልታ፡ ወኵናተ፤ ረምኃ፡ ወአስይፍተ፡ አዕባነ፡ ወቀስተ፡ ይኵኑ፡ 
                                ዝርዋነ፡ ከመ፡ ጸበል፡ ወጊሜ፡ ወይኅልቁ፡ ከመ፡ ጢስ፡ ሊተኒ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i14">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7011RespectMoses">Habani ḫāyla gǝrmā wa-mogas...</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the first or second column under the eleventh picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ሀበኒ፡ ኃይለ፡ ግርማ፡ ወሞገስ፡ ዘከመ፡ ወሀብኮ፡ ለሙሴ፡ ገበርከ፡ በቅድመ፡ ፈርዖን፡ ንጉሠ፡ ግብጽ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> 
                                ከማሁ፡ አስጥሞሙ፡ ለጸርየ፡ ወለጸላእት<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">የ፡</supplied> ሊተ፡ ለገብርከ፡ 
                                <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i15">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7012Enemies">Wa-soba yǝreʾǝyu kʷǝllomu gabarta ʿāmaṣā...</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the first or second column under the eleventh picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ይሬእዩ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ገበርተ፡ ዓመፃ፡ ይባዕ፡ ውስተ፡ ልቦሙ፡ ፍርሀት፡ ወረዓድ፡ ዘአንስት፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/>
                                ከማሁ፡ አጽልሞሙ፡ ወአእዑር፡ አዕይንቲሆሙ፡ ወአብህም፡ አፉሆሙ፡ ለአረሚ፡ ወለኵሎሙ፡ ገበርተ፡ ዓመፃ፡ እለ፡ ይመጽኡ፡ ኀቤየ፡ ለቀቲለ፡ ሰብእናየ፡ ሊተ፡ ለገብርከ፡
                                <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i16">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer against all persons doing injustice to the owner of this scroll</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the third column under the eleventh picture. It may contain an allusion to 
                                <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Psalm 92:7</ref>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">አስማተ፡ መሸብር፡ ርብሽመ፡ ርብሽመ፡ ርብሽመ፡ ርብሽአ፡ ርብሽአ፡ ርብሽአ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ አሸብሮሙ፡ ወአርዕዶሙ፡ ለኵሎሙ፡ 
                                ገበርተ፡ ዓመፃ፡ ለገበርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i17">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7129Protection">Ba-qǝdma ṣabʿ wa-qatl</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the third and fourth column under the eleventh picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በቅድመ፡ ፀብዕ፡ ወቀትል፡ በቅድመ፡ ፈረስ፡ ወእግር፡ ውእቱ፡ መግረሬ፡ ፀር፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ከማሁ፡ ሠውረኒ፡ 
                                ወአድኅነኒ፡ እምእደ፡ ፀርየ፡ ወጸላእትየ፡ ሊተ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i18">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7119Yethafaru">Yǝtḫāfaru wa-yǝḫsaru kʷǝllomu ṣalāʾtəya...</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the fourth column under the eleventh picture.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ይትኃፈሩ፡ ወይኅሰሩ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ጸላእትየ፡ እለ፡ ይመክሩ፡ እኵየ፡ ላዕሌየ፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i19">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old Testament</title>
                            <note>The text is written under the twelfth and thirteenth pictures. Each prayer begins with 
                                <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡</foreign> ("When he cried") or 
                                <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሑ፡</foreign> ("When they cried") and is often continued with 
                                <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስመከ፡</foreign> ("your name").</note>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.1">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Moses">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Moses</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ሙሴ፡ ገበርከ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ጋዲን፡ ፈሊዖ፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.2">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Joshua">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Joshua</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ኢያሱ፡ ወልደ፡ ነዌ፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ገባዖን፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ደርታን፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.3">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Elijah">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Elijah</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ኤልያስ፡ ስመከ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ አቅርያኖስ፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.4">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Daniel">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Daniel</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ <supplied reason="omitted" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">ጸርሐ፡ </supplied>ዳንኤል፡ ስመከ፡ እንዘ፡
                                    ይብል፡ ዝራኤል፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.5">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Manasseh">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Manasseh</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ምናሴ፡ ስመከ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ቀለኤል፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.6">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#ThreeChildren">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of the Three Holy Children in the Furnace (ʾĀnānyā, ʾĀzāryā and Misāʾel)</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሑ፡ አናንያ፡ ወአዛርያ፡ ወሚሳኤል፡ እንዘ፡ ይብሉ፡ ዳፋኤል፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.7">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#David">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of David</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ዳዊት፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ በለማዊፒሲል፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.8">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Hezekiah">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Hezekiah</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ሕዝቅያስ፡ ስመከ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ወገላውዮስ፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.9">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Jonah">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Jonah</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ <sic>ዳዊት፡</sic> ዮናስ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ዳላዊ፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i19.10">
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7103PrayOTprophets#Jeremiah">Collection of prayers of the prophets of the Old
          Testament (ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ስመከ፡ ...): Prayer of Jeremiah</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ጸርሐ፡ ኤርምያስ፡ ስመከ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ገደላፊል፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i20">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7130HaylaTsalai">Ṣalot baʾǝnta ḫayla ṣalāʾi wa-ḍar</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the second, third or fourth column under the twelfth picture interrupting the surrounding
                                text of <ref target="#ms_i19"/>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ 
                                ኃ<supplied reason="omitted" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">ይለ</supplied>፡ ፀላዒ፡ ወፀር፡ ወበእንተ፡ ኵናት፡ ዕንቋዕ፡ ይትፌሥሑ፡ 
                                ወይትሐሠዩ፡ ብከ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ እለ፡ የኃሡከ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ወይበሉ፡ ዘልፈ፡ ዓቢይ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i21">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7131KwinatTsar">Nǝsəʾǝlaka wa-nāstabaqqʷǝʿāka baʾǝnta kʷināt wa-ḍar</title>
                            <note>The text is written in the second, third or fourth column under the twelfth picture interrupting the surrounding
                                text of <ref target="#ms_i19"/>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ንስእለከ፡ ወናስተበቁዓከ፡ በእንተ፡ ኵናት፡ ወፀር፡ ከመ፡ ታውድቆሙ፡ ለጸርየ፡ ወለፀላእትየ፡
                                ወከመ፡ ኢይን<supplied reason="omitted" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">ሥ</supplied>አኒ፡ ሞት፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ጌዜየ፡ ተማኅፀንኩ፡ በለዋችን፡ ስምከ፡ 
                                በአርዳድ፡ ስምከ፡ ስም፡ መግረሬ፡ ፀር፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez" otherLangs="am"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i22">
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">Prayer against enemies</title>
                            <note>The text is written in two columns under the fourteenth picture, the text in the first column is partly illegible.</note>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez">ፍዙዝ፡ ረስዮሙ፡ ለጸርየ፡ እለ፡ ይፀብዑኒ፡ አረሚ፡ ወክርስቲያን፡ ከዓውያነ፡ ደም፡ በሜሎስ፡ ገጽከ፡ በኬብሮን፡ ለግግ፡ ሕትሞሙ፡
                                በዚዛኤል፡ ወክክኤል፡ በአርቃድዮስ፡ ንጉሥ፡ በከመ፡ ተዓሥረ፡ በ፭፻፼፡ ሰናስለ፡ እሳት፡ ከማሁ፡ እስሮሙ፡ 
                                ለ<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH1508Gallai">ጋላ፡</persName> ወለ<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH2043sanqel">ሻንቅላ፡</persName>፡ ከመ፡ 
                                ኢይንሥኡ፡ ንዋይየ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ አድኅነኒ፡ እምፀርየ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/></explicit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
